p: Thin layer chromatography was further deciphered by mass spectrometry. LC-MS analysis of the BS was performed in negative ion mode. LC-MS data described the major ion peak of molecular mass m/z 195.14 ( Figure 4D) were observed predominantly as the terpenes produced by marine bacteria (4R,5Z)-dodec-5-en-4-olide ( De Carvalho and Fernandes, 2010).
